"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-brainstorm-2024-0725-1461557-irish-atheletes-olympic-medals-other-countries\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Oliver O\\\\u0027Hanlon  UCC  Analysis: Meet the Cork hammer thrower, the Antrim marathon runner, the Kerry rifle-shooter, the Louth archer and the Fermanagh sprinter  Before Ireland competed as an independent delegation at theOlympic Games in Paris in 1924, Irish-born people competed for other nations.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 71, \"end\": 77, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Antrim\", \"score\": 0.9999284202834988, \"rank\": 7.158484039454003e-05, \"text\": \"Antrim\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Antrim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Antrim\"}, {\"begin\": 99, \"end\": 104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Kerry\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.912989875140626e-13, \"text\": \"Kerry\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Kerry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Kerry\"}, {\"begin\": 124, \"end\": 129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Louth\", \"score\": 0.7661764720475205, \"rank\": 0.30518233916448234, \"text\": \"Louth\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Louth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Louth\"}, {\"begin\": 241, \"end\": 246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999928568286, \"rank\": 7.143165737212676e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most competed for the United Kingdom, of which Ireland was a part until 1922, but several Irish-born athletes also competed for other nations in the early to mid-1900s.\", \"from\": 302, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 324, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7542315625072653, \"rank\": 0.3244673781596695, \"text\": \"United Kingdom\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 349, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9941130204976926, \"rank\": 0.005921841260238381, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was usually the United States and Canada or, in one case, South Africa - countries where the athletes had settled after emigration.\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9891905745798071, \"rank\": 0.01086055412492493, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 510, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9260821091734416, \"rank\": 0.07952605819644155, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the athletes were victorious and brought medals back to their respective new homelands.\", \"from\": 608, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh represented Canada in the hammer throw at the1908 Games in London.\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 723, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9260821091734416, \"rank\": 0.07952605819644155, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9999999939304871, \"rank\": 6.069627242347086e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_GAA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From Carriganima near Macroom, he played for Cork in the1899and1901All-Ireland football finals.\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macroom\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.661459145077537e-15, \"text\": \"Macroom\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macroom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macroom\"}, {\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Cork\", \"score\": 0.7660933109300765, \"rank\": 0.3053239985219139, \"text\": \"Cork\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Cork\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Cork\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh took part in the local sports in Macroom and he almost beat the 56lb weight throwing world record in 1904 with a throw of 27 foot 2 inches.\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 1019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 913, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macroom\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.661459145077537e-15, \"text\": \"Macroom\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macroom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Macroom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won several GAA football place-kicking titles in the early 1900s.\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After a move to America in 1907, Walsh became a member of theIrish American Athletic Club of New York, many of whose members worked for theNew York City Police Department.\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999719654225208, \"rank\": 2.2503794899550413e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1183, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9999701993590278, \"rank\": 2.9801528911708025e-05, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_GAA\"}, {\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police\", \"score\": 0.9780318712627404, \"rank\": 0.02184175853748601, \"text\": \"Police Department\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh was one of the so-called'Irish Whales', a group of eight Irishmen who dominated weight-throwing competitions and earned the nickname thanks to their tall and robust physiques.\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They managed to win an amazing 23 medals at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh won a bronze medal in the hammer throw at the 1908 Games for Canada, having moved there from New York in 1907.\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1569, \"end\": 1575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9260821091734416, \"rank\": 0.07952605819644155, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 1601, \"end\": 1609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9999701993590278, \"rank\": 2.9801528911708025e-05, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_GAA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McArthur represented South Africa in the marathon at the1912 Olympic Gamesin Stockholm.\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1641, \"end\": 1653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999990955075, \"rank\": 9.041691113955831e-10, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Born in Dervock, Co. Antrim, he emigrated to South Africa in 1901 at the age of 20, leaving behind his job as a postman.\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1753, \"end\": 1765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999990955075, \"rank\": 9.041691113955831e-10, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He joined the police and became a middle distance athlete.\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1887, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He trained by racing against a narrow-gauge railway train and won several competitions, including the South African cross country championships.\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1996, \"end\": 2031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Cross_Country_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999867127262961, \"rank\": 1.237092052752694e-05, \"text\": \"African cross country championships\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Cross_Country_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Cross_Country_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He took gold in the 1912 marathon with a time of 2 hours 36 minutes and 54 seconds, which was run in temperatures of around 32C.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"64 runners from 19 countries took part in the race and half of those who started were forced to retire before the finish due to the unbearably hot July heat.\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2320, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The race is notable as one of the participants, the Portuguese runnerFrancisco L\\u00e1zaro, died while taking part.\", \"from\": 2321, \"to\": 2431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2373, \"end\": 2383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\", \"score\": 0.7259393175399308, \"rank\": 0.3719699073721206, \"text\": \"Portuguese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His death is recorded as the first ever fatality during an Olympic event.\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2505, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From BBC Northern Ireland, the story of Kennedy \\\"Ken\\\" McArthur, the Northern Irish man who won the 1912 Olympic marathon for South Africa  The bronze medal went to another South African runner,Christian Gitsham.\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2514, \"end\": 2517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9796726921770057, \"rank\": 0.019055784755939536, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.415095007479029e-20, \"text\": \"Northern Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 2549, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\", \"score\": 0.9999822374738452, \"rank\": 1.77628405596043e-05, \"text\": \"Kennedy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_F._Kennedy\"}, {\"begin\": 2577, \"end\": 2591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"score\": 0.9999999999031388, \"rank\": 9.675117778608343e-11, \"text\": \"Northern Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2634, \"end\": 2646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999990955075, \"rank\": 9.041691113955831e-10, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 2702, \"end\": 2719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Gitsham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian Gitsham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Gitsham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_Gitsham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McArthur and Gitsham had shared the lead in the race at the 17-mile mark.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2794, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gitsham stopped for water with two miles to go and came in around one minute after McArthur, who also took home a floating trophy and a bronze statue along with his gold medal.\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 2971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The statue was ofPheidippides, the man who is said to have run from Marathon to Athens to alert the authorities of the Athenian victory in the Battle of Marathon.\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 3134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3040, \"end\": 3048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3649238353983146e-23, \"text\": \"Marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marathon\"}, {\"begin\": 3052, \"end\": 3058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999995055519634, \"rank\": 4.944480893686198e-07, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3091, \"end\": 3099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.136179965670927e-13, \"text\": \"Athenian\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was donated by the King of Greece.\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3172, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is anathletics stadiumnamed for McArthur in his adopted hometown of Potchefstroom.\", \"from\": 3173, \"to\": 3261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3247, \"end\": 3260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Potchefstroom\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.286156337090296e-14, \"text\": \"Potchefstroom\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Potchefstroom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Potchefstroom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fenton was born in the Gaeltacht village of Ventry in Co. Kerry.\", \"from\": 3263, \"to\": 3327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3321, \"end\": 3326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Kerry\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.912989875140626e-13, \"text\": \"Kerry\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Kerry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Kerry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He emigrated to the United States in 1906 and eventually joined the army.\", \"from\": 3328, \"to\": 3401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3348, \"end\": 3361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9891905745798071, \"rank\": 0.01086055412492493, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was stationed in the Philippines for a time, where he developed his rifle skills on the shooting range.\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3426, \"end\": 3437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9886925708382507, \"rank\": 0.010522294729397006, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fenton served briefly in China and helped to train recruits in Arizona during the First World War.\", \"from\": 3509, \"to\": 3607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3534, \"end\": 3539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.998651361251042, \"rank\": 0.0005200411433834577, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3572, \"end\": 3579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona\", \"score\": 0.990087081347655, \"rank\": 0.004950441483851969, \"text\": \"Arizona\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He represented the US in shooting at the1920 Olympic Games in Antwerpand the 1924 Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 3609, \"to\": 3706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3628, \"end\": 3630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9356424372020338, \"rank\": 0.06878228845087372, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3700, \"end\": 3705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999928568286, \"rank\": 7.143165737212676e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won three golds in the team shooting events and a bronze in the individual small-bore rifle contest in Antwerp and a bronze in Paris.\", \"from\": 3707, \"to\": 3843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3813, \"end\": 3820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\", \"score\": 0.9999756704332149, \"rank\": 2.4306069328279866e-05, \"text\": \"Antwerp\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\"}, {\"begin\": 3837, \"end\": 3842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999928568286, \"rank\": 7.143165737212676e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze he won at the team event in Paris in 1924 was known as the'100 meter running deer'as it involved competitors shooting at a deer-shaped target.\", \"from\": 3844, \"to\": 3997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3883, \"end\": 3888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999928568286, \"rank\": 7.143165737212676e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity.\", \"from\": 3999, \"to\": 4166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences  \\u00d3 RT\\u00c9 Raidi\\u00f3 na Gaeltachta Sao