ntence\": \"She had been competing in archery competitions since the late 1890s.\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Archery was one of the only sports open to women at the 1908 Games in London.\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4623, \"end\": 4630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\", \"score\": 0.9999872893789136, \"rank\": 1.2710782537332475e-05, \"text\": \"Archery\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archery\"}, {\"begin\": 4693, \"end\": 4699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9999999939304871, \"rank\": 6.069627242347086e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_GAA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of the 25 competitors in the women's event represented Great Britain, guaranteeing them all three medals.\", \"from\": 4701, \"to\": 4810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4760, \"end\": 4773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.8168316094320527e-13, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze medal that she won in 1908 is now in theCounty Museum in Dundalk.\", \"from\": 4811, \"to\": 4887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4879, \"end\": 4886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dundalk\", \"score\": 0.9999999999758984, \"rank\": 2.4305048417894265e-11, \"text\": \"Dundalk\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dundalk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dundalk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kerr represented Canada at the1904 Games in St. Louisand the 1908 Games in London.\", \"from\": 4889, \